Show HN: We built a ChatGPT sidebar (annoyed by the popup)
text: Hey!HNs,so, I’ve been using ChatGPT a lot lately and experimented with a lot of their chrome extensions. But, I gotta admit, one thing that bugged me was those popups that would vanish as soon as I clicked away. That’s why my partner and I decided to build a sidebar instead. We’re pretty stoked about it and would love to hear your thoughts too! So, hit us up with all your feedback!

title: Repeat yourself, do more than one thing (2018)
Why people make a living online out of courses on how to make a living online?
text:
A recurring theme I see in the indie hacking community is selling a course or an e-book into how to be an indie hacker.

Why is this so prevalent and people see it as a viable strategy instead of focusing on product and customers?
